Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Remove the core from the @red pepper{2}(sliced lengthways into ½cm strips) and slice lengthways into ½cm strips. Mix your pepper with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{pinch} and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Place on a #baking tray{} in your oven for ~{15%minutes}.

Boil a large #pot{} of water. Peel and grate the @garlic{4%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Tear the @fresh basil{1}(torn into small pieces) leaves into small pieces.

> Tearing basil leaves releases more flavour than chopping.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{splash} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium heat. Fry the @British smoked bacon lardons{3}(until crispy) until it is crispy around the edges.

Add your garlic and cook for ~{2%minutes}.

> Avoid overcooking the garlic as you don't want it to taste bitter.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{2%400g cans} with the @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp} (add more or less depending on how spicy you like it). Add a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook on medium heat for around ~{10%minutes}, until you have a nice thick tomato sauce.

Cook the @wheat penne pasta{400%g} in the boiling water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for around ~{6%minutes}, until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

Once your pasta is cooked, drain and then stir it into your tomato sauce. When your pepper is nice and soft, add this to your tomato sauce too.

Scatter your basil leaves over your pasta. Grate the @parmesan cheese{40%g}(grated) on top and dig in!

> Best eaten with a fork, in a reclined position, on the sofa.